# Public profile pages: https://getplatform.pages.dev/profile/@clover
# One simple 200 rewrite. Any /profile/@something path is served by the same
# profile/index.html that already exists for your OWN profile page -- the
# page itself checks the URL to tell the two cases apart (see profile/index.html).
#
# Two things that broke this before, now avoided on purpose:
#   1. Cloudflare Pages only understands the "*" wildcard + ":splat" -- it
#      does NOT support Netlify-style named placeholders like ":username".
#   2. The destination is the FOLDER "/profile/", not "/profile/index.html".
#      Naming index.html explicitly triggers Cloudflare's automatic
#      "clean URLs" redirect, which strips query strings and undoes the rewrite.
/profile/@*    /profile/?u=:splat   200

# In-page video watch: https://getplatform.pages.dev/watch/dQw4w9WgXcQ
# Same trick as above, scoped to /watch/ this time (not the whole site --
# a bare "/*" catch-all would swallow every 404/typo into the homepage,
# which we don't want). watch/index.html checks ?v= for the id and calls
# the video-lookup edge function; if it's not a real Platform video it
# shows a 404 in place of just the player, everything else on the page
# stays put.
/watch/*    /watch/?v=:splat   200
